      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Ansys Mechanical R2023 and FDA in-house FEA code both hold current ISO 9001 certificates; version control and regression test suite documented in software quality plan SQP-FEA-2023-001. Required level 2 satisfied when a documented quality plan with traceability to solver version is on file.",
      "rationale": "Commercial solver (Ansys Mechanical R2023) operates under an ISO 9001-certified quality management system. FDA in-house code is managed under FDA OC SQA procedures. Regression test suite executed prior to each simulation campaign; results archived in FDA EDMS."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification is considered adequate at level 2 when benchmark problems with known analytical solutions (beam bending, Hertzian contact) are solved to within 1% relative error and results are documented in a verification report. Ansys benchmark suite VER-ANS-2023 and FDA benchmark report BM-FEA-2021 satisfy this criterion.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical passes published ASME V&V 10 benchmark suite. FDA in-house code verified against Timoshenko beam and Hertzian contact analytical solutions (relative error < 0.5%). Verification reports archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal mesh convergence study with at least three element densities must demonstrate that key QoIs (stiffness, yield force) change by less than 2% between the two finest meshes. The converged mesh must be documented and used for all production runs.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed across three element sizes (coarse 2 mm, medium 1 mm, fine 0.5 mm). Stiffness QoI changed by 1.3% between medium and fine meshes; yield force changed by 0.8%. Fine mesh (0.5 mm global, 0.25 mm at screw-rod interface) adopted for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Standard solver tolerances applied. Convergence checked."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Simulation inputs reviewed by a second analyst."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form adequacy at level 3 requires that the constitutive law (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) is justified by coupon-level material test data and that contact mechanics formulation is documented. Justification must appear in a model description report reviewed by a subject-matter expert.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening constitutive model for Ti-6Al-4V justified by tensile coupon data (n=5 coupons per lot). Augmented Lagrange contact formulation selected based on prior literature. Model description report MDR-FEA-SCREW-001 reviewed and approved by biomechanics SME."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Level 3 requires that all material and geometric inputs are traceable to measured values with stated uncertainties. Nominal geometry must be verified against CMM measurements within ±0.05 mm. Material properties must be derived from lot-specific coupon tests.",
      "rationale": "Geometry inputs derived from CMM measurements of production screws (n=5 per lot); nominal dimensions within ±0.03 mm of CAD nominal. Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.2 GPa) from lot-specific coupon tests. UHMWPE block properties from supplier datasheet with ±5% uncertainty bounds applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Level 3 requires N≥10 test specimens drawn from at least two independent lots, with dimensional inspection confirming conformance to drawing tolerances. Inter-laboratory testing at two or more sites is strongly preferred.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA OSEL and DePuy Synthes). Specimens drawn from two production lots. Dimensional inspection confirmed all screws within drawing tolerances. Inter-laboratory variability assessed via Levene test (p=0.34, no significant difference in variance)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single load condition (ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending at 5 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Only one test condition evaluated; loading rate sensitivity and temperature effects not explored. This shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Model inputs confirmed equivalent to test conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric E/uval must be less than 1.96 for each QoI (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement), and the absolute percentage difference between mean FEA prediction and mean experimental result must be less than 10% for each QoI.",
      "rationale": "E/uval = 0.87 (stiffness), 1.12 (yield force), 0.94 (force at 40 mm). All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96. Absolute percentage differences: stiffness 3.2%, yield force 4.8%, force at 40 mm 2.9%. All within the 10% acceptance bound."
    },
